3yw.title: Submitting a page to a domain
3yw.clickbait: How and why to submit a page to a domain
3yw.text:
Every logged in user can create a [16x page] on Arbital, but unless you are already a [5fs trusted] in a [14z domain], you have to submit the page for approval before it appears in the domain. This way a page can be reviewed by experienced authors before it's visible to the general public.

The process for submitting a page is simple:

1. Create a [new page](https://arbital.com/edit).
2. Publish it. (The page is now [3yx unlisted].)
3. Click "submit to math domain" button.
4. One of the [5ft reviewers] will take a look. If the page can looks useful, they'll leave a comment. Otherwise, they'll approve the page.
5. Once you've submitted enough high quality pages, you'll become a member of the domain, and will be able to skip this approval process.
